==English==
===Etymology===
From ancient Greek [[αυτοκρατής]] (''autokrates'') "one who governs alone" , from [[αυτός]] (''autos'') "single, self, same, alone" + [[κράτος]] (''kratos'') "power".

===Noun===
'''autocracy'''
# form of [[government]] in which unlimited power is held by a single [[individual]]
